==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refinery
<hw>Re*fin"er*y</hw> <pr>(-?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Refineries</plw> <pr>(-<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>raffinerie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The building and
apparatus for refining or purifying, esp. metals and sugar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A furnace in which cast iron is refined by the
action of a blast on the molten metal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refit</ent>⟦br⟧
